<br>
I truely sympathize her loss, but I also sympathize for anyone who may become the victums of someone lashing out, she'll have no problem finding people to help lash out, especially people with an agenda, if that happens, I hope she can spot it before she becomes part of something, that she wouldn't want to be a part of, sometimes a crusade, can be nothing more than a self-serving agenda, nothing wrong with that, as long as it doesn't hurt innocent people. /shrug<br>
<br>
This topic sparked my interest, because my best friend who died at the age of 25 due to a rare bone cancer, had gone through experimental surgery, and eventually lost a leg, he had been walking for 6+ months on a crushed hipbone, though in pain, he never talked about it, other &quot;severe&quot; things went on in his life as well, but he kept fighting the cancer, because he wanted to live, he once told me that it made him so sad when he would hear of people throwing their lives away, when he would give anything to just live another day.<br>
<br>
