<br>
Thomus hit it on the head with his post: people are always seeking for reasons why in a suicide, and most likely to point to the things they least understand as potential reasons.  Beyond this though is a point we all understand: Everquest can take its toll on our real lives.  Easy to justify intially, as a replacement to other popular diversions, such as tv, later as it consumes more of our time, those justifications can be a stretch.  I remember being fairly defensive about playing - and whether or not it was excessive - when I was questioned about it, and the hard part is that &quot;balance&quot; is a subjective judgement.<br>
<br>
I left the game after 2.5 years 3 months ago, and am happy with what my rediscovered RL has brought to me.  We are all different people, with different commitments in our lives; my suggestion is to look at your own and try to be happy without sacrificing things you may regret later.<br>
